                            <comment id="16423257" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 2 Apr 2018 22:56:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 2c1f110b6bf0053cfa50608a70454d9102744511 in lucene-solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tflobbe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tflobbe&quot;&gt;tflobbe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=2c1f110&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=2c1f110&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12172&quot; title=&quot;Race condition in collection properties can cause invalid cache of properties&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-12172&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-12172&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fixed race condition in collection properties&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16423260" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 2 Apr 2018 22:57:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit ca7d72a0700e7fe37cfc8b47c448cc2ff4b103e1 in lucene-solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/branch_7x from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tflobbe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tflobbe&quot;&gt;tflobbe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=ca7d72a&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=ca7d72a&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12172&quot; title=&quot;Race condition in collection properties can cause invalid cache of properties&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-12172&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-12172&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fixed race condition in collection properties&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16423500" author="shalinmangar" created="Tue, 3 Apr 2018 05:38:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tflobbe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tflobbe&quot;&gt;tflobbe&lt;/a&gt; &amp;#8211; I don&apos;t think we should introduce another thread(pool) just for this feature. We can use a method similar to updateWatchedCollection which checks if the new znode version is greater than the old one. This ensures that we replace the old collection props only if the new one is actually newer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16424689" author="tomasflobbe" created="Tue, 3 Apr 2018 22:17:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=shalin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;shalin&quot;&gt;shalin&lt;/a&gt;. I thought about doing something like that, but decided not to since it requires to keep something like a map with collection -&amp;gt; version and handling it made the code more complex. I&apos;ll put up a patch, maybe it&apos;s still better to go that route anyway&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16424785" author="tomasflobbe" created="Tue, 3 Apr 2018 23:59:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=shalin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;shalin&quot;&gt;shalin&lt;/a&gt;, just by keeping the synchronization I added to &lt;tt&gt;refreshAndWatch&lt;/tt&gt; in the previous commit we can guarantee that we won&apos;t be setting the collection property map to an older value, however, I don&apos;t think we can guarantee that the notifications to watchers won&apos;t be out of order without using the single thread executor. Are you suggesting that we go that way anyway?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16434567" author="tomasflobbe" created="Wed, 11 Apr 2018 20:58:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shalin, I created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12213&quot; title=&quot;Consider removing the collectionPropsNotifications thread from ZkStateReader&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-12213&quot;&gt;SOLR-12213&lt;/a&gt; to continue the discussion there. I&apos;ll resolve this one since the test bug is fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
